OL,3,CLabour's pledge not to raise working
OL,4,Cpeople's taxes 'not credible', IFS says
OL,6,FAnd the IFS calculates that "most" of
OL,7,Fany money raised would need to be
OL,8,Fspent protecting households from the
OL,9,Fpolicy's impact, particularly "those
OL,10,Fon lower incomes".
OL,12,FThe manifesto pledges made by the main
OL,13,Fparties are more modest but, in the
OL,14,FIFS's view, also suffer plausibility
OL,15,Fproblems.
OL,17,FThe IFS says the Tories would find
OL,18,Fcutting #12 billion from welfare
OL,19,Fspending "seriously tough."
