OL,3,CLabour's pledge not to raise working
OL,4,Cpeople's taxes 'not credible', IFS says
OL,6,FAnd Labour's promise not to increase
OL,7,Ftaxes on "working people" is one they
OL,8,Fwould struggle to keep.
OL,10,F"I don't think it's credible to say
OL,11,Fyou will not have any tax increases
OL,12,Fthat affect any working people," says
OL,13,FPaul Johnson, Director of the IFS.
OL,15,FIf Labour wins the election, the IFS
OL,16,Fcalculates spending on investment and
OL,17,Funprotected public services would
OL,18,Flikely be cut by around #22 billion a
OL,19,Fyear by the end of the next parliament.
