OL,3,CLabour's pledge not to raise working
OL,4,Cpeople's taxes 'not credible', IFS says
OL,6,FIf the Tories win, the cuts would be
OL,7,F#36 billion, in part because of the
OL,8,Fcommitment to raise defence spending.
OL,10,FThese are the funding black holes both
OL,11,Fparties still refuse to engage with.
OL,13,FBoth Labour and the Tories appear to
OL,14,Fbe banking on the economy suddenly
OL,15,Fbooming.
OL,17,FThe government's forecaster, the OBR,
OL,18,Fthinks the economy will grow by 1.8% a
OL,19,Fyear in the next parliament - that
OL,20,Fforecast is considered modest.
