OL,3,CLabour's pledge not to raise working
OL,4,Cpeople's taxes 'not credible', IFS says
OL,6,FThe IFS says, that if the next
OL,7,Fgovernment is lucky and growth comes
OL,8,Fin 0.5% a year higher - those spending
OL,9,Fcuts would disappear.
OL,11,FBut if growth comes in 0.5% lower than
OL,12,Fthe OBR forecast - and the Bank of
OL,13,FEngland thinks it will - then the
OL,14,Fscale of the cuts increases by another
OL,15,F#30 billion a year.
OL,17,F"Hoping for the best is not a
OL,18,Fstrategy," says Mr Johnson. "The key
OL,19,Fquestion to ask of those seeking our
OL,20,Fvotes on July 4th is how would they
OL,21,Frespond to such bad economic news."
