OL,3,CLabour's pledge not to raise working
OL,4,Cpeople's taxes 'not credible', IFS says
OL,6,FThe IFS says the next government faces
OL,7,Fa "trilemma": raise taxes by more than
OL,8,Fset out in the manifesto, cut spending
OL,9,For borrow more and we can only guess
OL,10,Fat what the parties would do.
OL,12,FLabour and the Tories have already
OL,13,Fruled out increases to the three big
OL,14,Ftaxes - income tax, national insurance
OL,15,Fand VAT - which together raise just
OL,16,Fover 60% of revenues.
OL,18,FIn theory, there's room to raise tax
OL,19,Felsewhere but the IFS says it's "hard
OL,20,Fto get anything substantial" by hiking
OL,21,FInheritance Tax or Capital Gains.
